The paper discusses visual information manipulation and scene understanding, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method also involves iterative analysis and heuristic methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG a likely sub-category. The use of graphs and traversal algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of computational geometry (cs.GR). Finally, the study focuses on human cognitive abilities and perception, indicating a potential fit for the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
